==English==
===Etymology===
[[ante-]] + L ''[[diluvium]]'' {[[flood]]}

===Adjective===
'''antediluvian'''

# Extremely [[Ancient]] or [[antiquated]]; [[old]].
# Pertaining or belonging to the time prior to [[Noah]]'s [[Flood]].
# Supremely [[dated]] e.g. 'Those ideas are antediluvian.'
{{seeCites}}
